{"title":"Far Tratamiento de Diabetes Mellitus Tipo 2-2024-1","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/Endocrinología/Far Tratamiento de Diabetes Mellitus Tipo 2-2024-1.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Tratamiento del Diabetes Mellitus Tipo 2\\N(T2DM)","guid":"_fOH7jJOLSaZ7zeNQKTArw","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Resumen","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"• Varios avances recientes → múltiples beneficios para personas con T2DM\\N(Keong Chong et al.).","guid":"hccnUStCvssOxgvXZOO2lA","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"• Terapia farmacológica guiada por factores centrados en la persona\\N(comorbilidades, objetivos de tratamiento).","guid":"EWFkiCk8ycnkA_RrG1p5Jg","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"Pacientes con T2DM y\\Nalto riesgo de:","guid":"UeCmJpAfMj_SQT-YbGxv5w","children":[{"id":"5","parent":"4","text":"1. Enfermedad cardiovascular aterosclerótica (ECVA)","guid":"LiCgV99UMlmxjOqYqcFKAg","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"4","text":"2. Insuficiencia cardíaca (IC)","guid":"-kwvVgbD7MOIrKjeFl2TXw","children":[]},{"id":"7","parent":"4","text":"3. Enfermedad renal crónica (ERC)","guid":"0VpCPFXUrA-idbk3ajsD-A","children":[]}]},{"id":"8","parent":"1","text":"Requieren:","guid":"vwbYsDVgrixDIz3CR2YmFQ","children":[{"id":"9","parent":"8","text":"• Régimen de tratamiento que incluye agentes que ↓ riesgo cardiorrenal (Lee-Ming Chuang et al.).","guid":"vpwUDkBz44gLhiftiWVrpA","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"8","text":"Manejo de Peso","guid":"Y0FCLiXRccREn7xRzTS2aQ","children":[{"id":"11","parent":"10","text":"• Papel clave en ↓ glucosa para pacientes con T2DM.","guid":"XFnWkgmFznM5bZFi4o0eGg","children":[]},{"id":"12","parent":"10","text":"• Consideración del manejo de peso en el tratamiento de reducción de glucosa.","guid":"a19kZvN46hB22LiS9lVGTQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"13","parent":"1","text":"Inhibidores de SGLT2","guid":"UlrJWkZT2yQKYCRE2qDMgQ","children":[{"id":"14","parent":"13","text":"• ↓ riesgo de IC, eventos cardiovasculares y renales.","guid":"Xk46wXvFaC-KaWK25oANsw","children":[]}]},{"id":"15","parent":"1","text":"Agonistas del\\NReceptor de GLP-1","guid":"2koNuwNj1BELQSmVCHt5Jw","children":[{"id":"16","parent":"15","text":"• Mejor control de glucemia.","guid":"vZgaKUmEWxDxVCHJlpcXKg","children":[]},{"id":"17","parent":"15","text":"• Promueven pérdida de peso.","guid":"Sy1xJ-XCDhLFLTjhTha3CA","children":[]},{"id":"18","parent":"15","text":"• ↓ riesgo de eventos cardiovasculares.","guid":"6dvkr1A-rxozqWv_n3h_Iw","children":[]}]},{"id":"19","parent":"1","text":"Agonistas Dual de\\NGIP y GLP-1","guid":"A3dKeE460gwtAwSdJ_FszQ","children":[{"id":"20","parent":"19","text":"• Activan receptores de GIP y GLP-1.","guid":"xLuiAr9XYl_QykQ5U0UXqw","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"19","text":"• Mejoran control glucémico.","guid":"0QOwg9ejnIPu_gdHl6m08Q","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"19","text":"• Promueven mayor pérdida de peso que los agonistas del receptor de GLP-1.","guid":"_5voJb4J0XVGpKrD_k-x6A","children":[]}]},{"id":"23","parent":"1","text":"Nuevos Fármacos en\\NDesarrollo Clínico","guid":"s7EXZx7vxA2jjAbUol5fHw","children":[{"id":"24","parent":"23","text":"• Insulina Icodec.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"25","parent":"23","text":"• Retatrutida.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"23","text":"• Tirzepatida.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"27","parent":"0","text":"Cambios en el\\NTratamiento de T2DM","guid":"TgZMA5GayEEH20bJqhzqDA","children":[{"id":"28","parent":"27","text":"Antes de 2018:","guid":"rp-moCNm4eeiK_-t3OjHxA","children":[{"id":"29","parent":"28","text":"• Metformina como fármaco de primera línea.","guid":"1qIu-IK4SgCO-tAlECkiIA","children":[]},{"id":"30","parent":"28","text":"• Si no se alcanza el objetivo de HbA1c, se añaden otros agentes antidiabéticos de forma secuencial.","guid":"dgcmxbReHU1liu35xYstFA","children":[]}]},{"id":"31","parent":"27","text":"Evolución del\\Nenfoque:","guid":"8B9FkkWjMtLU9Tq2VHWrOg","children":[{"id":"32","parent":"31","text":"• De centrado en glucosa a\\Ntratamiento individual:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"33","parent":"32","text":"• Metas específicas de glucosa y peso.","guid":"gHJErIxs8JzmYta92lBbwQ","children":[]},{"id":"34","parent":"32","text":"• Consideración del riesgo de hipoglucemia y complicaciones cardiovasculares y renales.","guid":"hEo3Q0yOauLAvYUmMece4g","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"32","text":"• Importancia de la accesibilidad, costo y disponibilidad de medicamentos.","guid":"D3e1JBolcgNWqDSYmJBInQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"36","parent":"31","text":"• Enfoque holístico y centrado en el paciente → mejora de resultados y calidad de vida (ADA y EASD, 2022).","guid":"vhr39VdumG3f7ou5E8eL4Q","children":[]},{"id":"37","parent":"31","text":"• De secuencial a\\Ncombinación temprana:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"38","parent":"37","text":"• Enfoque actual: combinación temprana de medicamentos para mejorar los resultados cardiorrenales,\\Nindependientemente de los niveles de A1C o uso de metformina (ADA y EASD, 2022).","guid":"Khmnu7a6yKTRTQFb5ngjVA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"39","parent":"27","text":"Importancia del\\NManejo de Peso","guid":"K3ilVH7sNtj0plYomptSVw","children":[{"id":"40","parent":"39","text":"• Obesidad y exceso de peso → factores de riesgo para T2DM.","guid":"lKiyd_vc7wQyMGYf9oeBDg","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"39","text":"• Pérdida de peso mejora control glucémico y reduce riesgo de complicaciones.","guid":"c-nyHVkw2jdLfsMMXToNvg","children":[]},{"id":"42","parent":"39","text":"• Remisión de diabetes posible con pérdida de ≥15% de peso.","guid":"VedTYz4c0kM-R9H1ZYv96g","children":[]},{"id":"43","parent":"39","text":"• Manejo de obesidad → pilar en tratamiento de T2DM relacionado con adiposidad (ADA y EASD, 2022).","guid":"bUaVU6gUGkN9JbrJz5ZCcg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"44","parent":"0","text":"Metformina","guid":"qPW6qAMn5kI1vHnaaNU0IQ","children":[]},{"id":"45","parent":"0","text":"Sulfonilureas","guid":"7eaYmEC5MF7OpK0GeRWSyA","children":[]},{"id":"46","parent":"0","text":"Inhibidores de SGLT2\\N(SGLT2i)","guid":"a1lk3-cUGVH-IAm4Y2qktA","children":[]},{"id":"47","parent":"0","text":"Agonistas del Receptor GLP-1\\N(GLP-1 RA)","guid":"mXzaBRg6BgONDaJJy2ZW3A","children":[]},{"id":"48","parent":"0","text":"Agonista Dual de GLP-1 y GIP\\N(Tirzepatida)","guid":"0f0w_y_Q6Bv_yh5TMx-GJQ","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"0","text":"Nuevos Agentes\\Nen Desarrollo","guid":"sunCP6jvm9ufr8oO-tsENg","children":[{"id":"50","parent":"49","text":"4.1 Agonistas Dual de\\NReceptores de Amilina/GLP-1","guid":"zTHIzKY0McRrp3IGbVfDBA","children":[{"id":"51","parent":"50","text":"• Amilina: hormona de células de los islotes\\Npancreáticos, co-secretada con insulina.","guid":"a4ShBkgLk9yjVWwxDgwVwA","children":[{"id":"52","parent":"51","text":"• Suprime glucagón postprandial.","guid":"10ui4f2X-HNxudpjoVfA_Q","children":[]},{"id":"53","parent":"51","text":"• Retrasa vaciamiento gástrico.","guid":"dBVo48UEyOzD0QGgVZnEzQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"54","parent":"50","text":"• Cagrilintida: análogo semanal de\\Nacción prolongada de amilina.","guid":"vkcbvgBe9BeTizJA-xXOqg","children":[{"id":"55","parent":"54","text":"• Monoterapia o combinado con semaglutida.","guid":"DaSX9zs6S_RhEE1Hi8ZDDA","children":[]}]},{"id":"56","parent":"50","text":"• Ensayo fase 2\\N(32 semanas):","guid":"fLstUVus4C5qN8Fa1RQDrA","children":[{"id":"57","parent":"56","text":"• HbA1c: ↓ 2.2% (CagriSema), ↓ 1.8% (semaglutida), ↓ 0.9% (cagrilintida).","guid":"sWpe5-2Zlk0YVvQa8FKXfw","children":[]},{"id":"58","parent":"56","text":"• Peso: ↓ 15.6% (CagriSema), ↓ 5.1% (semaglutida), ↓ 8.1% (cagrilintida) (43, 44).","guid":"AJtz_fGYmlAt-W9H_d0Uww","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"59","parent":"49","text":"4.2 Agonistas Triple de Receptores\\NGIP/Glucagón/GLP-1","guid":"m5TmHWRVW3-rPiiQo3ML5w","children":[{"id":"60","parent":"59","text":"• Glucagón: péptido de 29 aminoácidos,\\Nestimula glucogenólisis y gluconeogénesis.","guid":"6OgZ6xklXmcwxy12WYoxMg","children":[{"id":"61","parent":"60","text":"• ↑ glucosa sanguínea.","guid":"mQYDCMozGN2J63yKCBCxlg","children":[]}]},{"id":"62","parent":"59","text":"• Retatrutida: agonista triple semanal de GIP/GLP-1/glucagón.","guid":"5_t4jEDiaYmg8hsPO0Zhxw","children":[{"id":"63","parent":"62","text":"• Administración IV.","guid":"sksWY456i3RyKZR8GxZQmA","children":[]}]},{"id":"64","parent":"59","text":"• Ensayo fase 2\\N(24 semanas):","guid":"fvIjIQKNqxChG5acivO2HA","children":[{"id":"65","parent":"64","text":"• HbA1c: cambios desde línea base → 0.01% (placebo), 1.41% (dulaglutida), 2.02% (retatrutida).","guid":"LmcQXYzN7-W_6LbXG7tQ2g","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"64","text":"• Peso: ↓ 3.00% - 16.94%, dependiente de la dosis (45).","guid":"cIugWbh1QUSEzHaV9UN8nw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"67","parent":"49","text":"4.3 Agonista Oral no\\NPeptídico del Receptor GLP-1","guid":"hE0r2-jG7p_4hKxXOIUO6g","children":[{"id":"68","parent":"67","text":"• Orforglipron","guid":"HLiFxgInxJAlgcDlU4K48g","children":[{"id":"69","parent":"68","text":"• Biodisponibilidad oral favorable (20%-40%).","guid":"z3MLfyP04itr5OzeLIxU1w","children":[]},{"id":"70","parent":"68","text":"• Vida media: 29-49 h.","guid":"EkS6Fq5lcwti_t-gQL-E_w","children":[]}]},{"id":"71","parent":"67","text":"• Ensayo fase 2\\N(26 semanas):","guid":"","children":[{"id":"72","parent":"71","text":"• HbA1c: ↓ 2.10% (orforglipron), ↓ 1.10% (dulaglutida).","guid":"jQmTD7pL5l0RNWzAixlNOg","children":[]},{"id":"73","parent":"71","text":"• Peso: ↓ 10.1 kg (orforglipron), ↓ 3.9 kg (dulaglutida) (46).","guid":"cWmH8_2GjkP92iz9j5jcQA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"74","parent":"49","text":"4.4 Análogo de\\NInsulina Basal Semanal","guid":"nZIdgA70hDZVjYH6REEm_Q","children":[{"id":"75","parent":"74","text":"• Insulina icodec: análogo de insulina acilado\\Ncon cadena de diácido graso C20.","guid":"CL8tZEpaJVkCpxzWsb1DFw","children":[{"id":"76","parent":"75","text":"• Unión reversible fuerte a albúmina.","guid":"vXDUf2DXzuVv0pkOGoO8xw","children":[]},{"id":"77","parent":"75","text":"• Reducción de afinidad por el receptor de insulina.","guid":"BHjNTXxmS1iEkqfS6KtzeQ","children":[]},{"id":"78","parent":"75","text":"• Modelo farmacodinámico de estado estacionario: efectos hipoglucémicos distribuidos uniformemente.","guid":"1nfxoh2mYSJFyMYYSTHOqw","children":[]}]},{"id":"79","parent":"74","text":"• Ensayo fase 3a\\N(52 semanas):","guid":"","children":[{"id":"80","parent":"79","text":"• HbA1c: ↓ 1.55% (icodec), ↓ 1. 35% (glargina U100).","guid":"SzGHYVXpnZdwWD5orNBD-Q","children":[]},{"id":"81","parent":"79","text":"• Tiempo en rango 70-180 mg/dL: 71.9% (icodec), 66.9% (glargina U100).","guid":"BtZpGjtDsnptmKmAGHVa-g","children":[]},{"id":"82","parent":"79","text":"• Eventos adversos similares en ambos grupos (47, 48).","guid":"Nl_rdGvUxQqn1qoGerkiNQ","children":[]}]}]}]}]},"node_count":82,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Endocrinología","folder":"Entidades clínicas/Endocrinología","filename":"Far Tratamiento de Diabetes Mellitus Tipo 2-2024-1","id":"map_575","resolved_references":[]}